name: Single Signal Cells #1
description:
Their is a single signal that instructs a cell what to build, a bioelectric code. If one alters this code, cells can be redirected to make changes to where and how things form. Single Signal Cells is a speculative notion of analog synthesis sending control voltage to the cell.  

Footage created at Signal Culture Artist Residency, utilizing Dave Jones MVIP and the Color Wobbulator.
